Name: glycogen metabolism disorder
Definition: A carbohydrate metabolism disorder that is characterized by abnormal accumulation or depletion of liver glycogen.

Name: NGLY1-deficiency
Definition: A carbohydrate metabolic disorder that is characterized by global developmental delay

Name: lactose intolerance
Definition: A tic disorder that is characterized by single or multiple motor or phonic tics

Name: hyperinsulinemic hypoglycemia
Definition: A carbohydrate metabolic disorder that involves low blood glucose resulting from an excess of insulin.

Name: obsolete lower limb lymph node mast cell malignancy
Definition: A carbohydrate metabolic disorder that involves low blood glucose resulting from an excess of insulin.
Synonym: Mast cell malignancy of lymph nodes of inguinal region and lower limb (disorder)

Name: obsolete Bunyaviridae infectious disease
Definition: A (-)ssRNA virus infectious disease that results_in infection in rodents and humans
Synonym: Mast cell malignancy of lymph nodes of inguinal region and lower limb (disorder)

Name: glucosephosphate dehydrogenase deficiency
Definition: A carbohydrate metabolic disorder that is characterised by abnormally low levels of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase (abbreviated G6PD or G6PDH).

Name: obsolete vision disorder
Definition: A carbohydrate metabolic disorder that is characterised by abnormally low levels of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase (abbreviated G6PD or G6PDH).

Name: primary hyperoxaluria
Definition: An autosomal recessive disease that has_material_basis_in rare mutations in two DNA excision repair proteins

Name: pyruvate decarboxylase deficiency
Definition: A carbohydrate metabolic disorder characterized by the buildup of lactic acid in the body and a variety of neurological problems and caused by a deficiency of one of the three enzymes in the pyruvate dehydrogenase complex.

Name: pyruvate carboxylase deficiency disease
Definition: A carbohydrate metabolic disorder that is characterized by deficiency of pyruvate carboxylase causing decreased utilization of carbohydrates and toxic accumulation of lactic acid

Name: fructose-1
Definition: A carbohydrate metabolic disorder that has_material_basis_in a deficiency of fructose-1

Name: obsolete inborn errors fructose metabolism
Definition: A carbohydrate metabolic disorder that has_material_basis_in a deficiency of fructose-1

Name: congenital disorder of glycosylation
Definition: A carbohydrate metabolic disorder that involves deficient or defective glycosylation of a variety of tissue proteins and/or lipids.

Name: hereditary fructose intolerance syndrome
Definition: An extrapulmonary tuberculosis that results in formation of tiny lesions in all the organs.

Name: galactosemia
Definition: A carbohydrate metabolic disorder that involves a defect in galactose metabolism resulting in toxic levels of galactose 1-phosphate in various tissues.
